Given an array arr[] of N integers, calculate the median

Example 1:
Input: N = 5
arr[] = 90 100 78 89 67
Output: 89
Explanation: After sorting the array 
middle element is the median 

Example 2:

Input: N = 4
arr[] = 56 67 30 79
Output: 61
Explanation: In case of even number of 
elements, average of two middle elements 
is the median.

For more reference check - https://practice.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/find-the-median0527/1?page=1&difficulty[]=-2&status[]=solved&category[]=Mathematical&sortBy=submissions
